    "Antidromic AVNRT is rare but important - mimics VT on ECG",
    "Cannot safely give adenosine without confirming no accessory pathway - risk of accelerating AF via pathway",
    "Delta waves may be visible at start of QRS if conduction begins via accessory pathway",
    "In practice: treat all regular wide-complex tachycardia as VT unless proven otherwise - safer default"
